{{Quote|We have thousands of probe droids searching the galaxy. I want proof, not leads!|[[Admiral]] [[Kendal Ozzel]]|<ref name="Episode V">{{Film|V}}</ref>|audio=Ozzel-ProbeDroids.flac}}
The '''Viper probe droid''', commonly referred to as the '''Imperial probe droid''', was a model of [[probe droid]] manufactured by [[Arakyd Industries]]<ref name="Updated and Expanded" /> that was used by the [[Galactic Empire]],<ref name="Databank Imperial probe droid" /> and later, the [[New Republic]],<ref name="Aftermath" /> for deep [[Realspace|space]] exploration and reconnaissance. The droid had five manipulator arms, a [[blaster]] and a communicator. They also featured a [[self-destruct mechanism]], [[repulsorlift]] [[engine]]s,<ref name="Databank Imperial probe droid" /> and a sensor suite.<ref name="Join the Battle">''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars: Character Encyclopedia - Join the Battle!]]''</ref> The [[11-3K viper probe droid|11-3K variant]] of the droid was used on [[Vandor]].<ref name="Solo">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref> During the [[Galactic Civil War]], [[Death Squadron]]<ref name="Episode V" /> launched [[Project Swarm]], an operation which deployed 100,000 Viper droids<ref name="Doctor Aphra 37">[[Doctor Aphra (2016) 37|''Doctor Aphra'' (2016) 37]]</ref> across the [[galaxy]] in [[hyperdrive pod]]s, in order to find the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebellion's]] [[Echo Base|base]]. A [[XJ9-CS14|probe]] deployed to the [[planet]] [[Hoth]] eventually found the base, which set into action the evacuation and [[Battle of Hoth|battle]] that took place soon after.<ref name="Episode V" /> The [[Rodian]] [[Gedeek Obaz]] designed the [[Alpha Droid]] variant for the Viper line during his service to the Empire but came to regret his decision.<ref name="Outlaws">''[[Star Wars Outlaws]]''</ref> After the [[Battle of Jakku|Fall of the Empire]], [[Gideon's Imperial remnant]] still used viper probe droids.<ref name="Chapter 23">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 23: The Spies}}</ref>

The droids communicated using [[Omnisignal unicode]].<ref name="Language">{{SWKidsYouTube|series=Star Wars By the Numbers|text=Every Language in Star Wars Movies|video=CZp8Civk2co|nolive=1}}</ref> Viper probe droids performed a large range of missions, from searching planets for signs of pirates and criminals. to conducting sensor scans of areas the Empire wanted to investigate. The droids used their sensors to probe wreckage and map terrain. They were equipped with powerful transceivers, which were used to relay their discoveries to [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer]]s and intelligence outposts for further analysis. Viper probe droids were also proficient at infiltration.<ref name="Join the Battle" />

